      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $node[\"Resume Parser\"].json.output }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are an ATS (Applicant Tracking System) simulator. Score strictly and consistently — identical resumes must get identical scores. Use this rubric, all scores 0-10:\n\n- ats_score: overall keyword density + parseability for ATS systems\n- format_score: standard section headers present, no missing contact info, consistent structure\n- projects_score: relevance, depth, and presence of quantified outcomes (numbers, %, impact)\n- skills_score: breadth + relevance of skills to target domain\n- experience_score: 0 if no work experience; otherwise score by action verbs + quantified impact\n- education_score: completeness and relevance\n\nBe a harsh grader. Average resumes = 4-6. Only exceptional, quantified, keyword-rich resumes get 8-10.\n\nOutput ONLY valid JSON: {ats_score, format_score, projects_score, skills_score, experience_score, education_score}"
        }
      },
